Dar es Salaam
Two bodies were Friday night found during a search and rescue operation after the historic House of Wonders in Zanzibar collapsed.
The building, also known as Beit AL Ajaib, was undergoing renovations when the incident happened on 25 December, 2020.
According to a statement issued by Zanzibar’s Minister for Tourism and Antiquities Lela Muhamed Mussa, the bodies were found at night while the rescue operation was underway.



